title: For Sale:  Pre-Ban AR-15 Complete Rifle
postcontent:
I have a very good condition, complete, Pre-Ban, AR-15 rifle for sale. It has a collapsible stock (which is legal because it is a pre-ban). The rifle has a legal, threaded barrel to accept a suppressor (not included). This rifle can legally be turned into a short barrel rifle (SBR), as well. Lots of fun can be had with this Pre-Ban rifle that is illegal with Post-Ban rifles. 

No one knows for sure what will happen in CT regarding firearms bans, but on the table is some legislation that will ban the sale of these weapons -- you will only be allowed to own them, which is the main reason I am selling. If I do not sell it soon, it is possible I will be stuck with it (as no one will be able to legally buy it) and I already have four others, which is more than enough for me. 

The rifle was manufactured by Olympic Arms and shoots very well. I am willing to meet at a range to shoot the firearm before purchase -- for the serious buyer only. I will also include a fully loaded, thirty round magazine with the rifle. I am asking a firm $3000. 

For those that don't know, it is the pre-ban, Lower Receiver, which this rifle is equipped with, that allows the components that are illegal on other rifles. I see a lot of guys charging insane amounts of money for pre-ban upper receivers. A pre-ban upper is worth just as much as a post-ban upper, maybe less because it is older and could have been fired a lot more.

Thank you

The Modular Upper Receiver (MUR) is a rigid MilSpec flat-top upper receiver made to fit all AR15/M16/M4 rifles and carbines. The MUR was developed to give the customer a MilSpec correct upper receiver with a thicker wall, making the MUR upper receiver a stronger platform. This more rigid upper receiver will increase accuracy and reliability, while extending the life of the interfacing components, such as the bolt carrier group and barrel assembly. 

The MUR is made from a 7075 aircraft-grade aluminum forging. Prior to machining, the forging is fully stress relieved, heat treated, aged twice and undergoes a proprietary cryogenic treatment. The MUR is precision machined and each part finished by hand. There is not a better upper receiver available.

postcontent: This is a brand new Heckler & Koch HK MR556 rifle for sale. A direct descendent of the HK416, the MR556A1 is a semi-automatic rifle developed by Heckler & Koch as a premium level commercial/civilian firearm with match rifle capability. Like the HK416, the MR556A1 is a major product improvement over conventional AR-type carbines and rifles. The MR556A1 uses the HK proprietary gas piston operating system, employing a piston and a solid operating “pusher” rod in place of the gas tube normally found in AR15/M16/M4-style firearms. The MR556A1 is produced in the USA using American and German made components. The MR556A1 uses many of the same assemblies and accessories originally developed for the HK416 including the HK free-floating four-quadrant rail system. The HK Free Floating Rail System (FFRS) handguard has four MIL-STD-1913 “Picatinny” rails and allows all current accessories, sights, lights, and aimers used on M4/M16-type arms to be fitted to the MR Series. The HK rail system can be installed and removed with simple tools and returns to zero when reinstalled. Like the famous HK416, the MR556A1 uses a German-made barrel produced by Heckler & Koch’s famous cold hammer forging process. The highest quality steel is used in this unique manufacturing process producing a barrel that provides superior accuracy and long service life. The MR556A1 is being produced with the same commitment to quality as German-made HK firearms. By using joint U.S./German manufacturing, Heckler & Koch leverages the relative strengths of two continents to make the preeminent AR-type firearm, combining the designs innovations of the USA and Germany into one new product. Like the famous HK416, the MR556A1 uses a German-made barrel produced by Heckler & Koch’s famous cold hammer forging process. title: For Sale:  35 Remington 8A take down rifle
postcontent:
Please contact me by phone if you are interested in this item.  REDACTED

Serial Number is 12587 and we are open to offers.  You don't see this gun for sale very often.

The Remington Model 8 rifle is long recoil-operated and uses a rotating bolt head. After firing, the barrel and bolt, still locked together, move rearward inside the receiver and compress two recoil springs. Then the bolt is held back while the barrel is returned forward by one of the springs permitting extraction and ejection. Once the barrel is returned, the bolt is returned forward by the second spring; in so doing it picks up a fresh round from the magazine and chambers it. The Remington Model 8 has a fixed 5-shot magazine and bolt hold-open device which engages after the magazine is empty. *** It is a takedown design, meaning that the barrel and receiver are easily separated with no tools, allowing for a smaller package for transport.

On October 16, 1900, John Browning was granted U.S. Patent 659,786 for the rifle, which he then sold to Remington. Outside the U.S., this rifle was made by Fabrique Nationale of Liege, Belgium, and marketed as the FN Browning 1900. Under an agreement between Remington and FN, the Model 8 would be sold in the US while the FN 1900 would be sold elsewhere. Despite having a larger market, the FN 1900 was sold predominately to hunters in and around Western Europe and Canada. Because of the new and yet unproven nature of the autoloading rifle, the FN model never experienced the same level of sales as the Model 8. Cameron Woodall of The Great Model 8, a website dedicated to the rifle, postulates that this was likely due to the difficulty convincing European hunters to spend money on an expensive rifle that few people had ever seen before. Due to lackluster sales, only 4,913 Model 1900s were ever produced compared to the over 80,000 Model 8s produced.
